message.content:
It seems there are a few typos in your question. I assume you are asking, "How many standard English phonemes exist?"

There is no universally agreed-upon number of phonemes in the English language, as different dialects and accents can have variations. However, it is generally accepted that there are around 44 distinct sounds or phonemes in the standard British English (Received Pronunciation) and General American accent. These include 24 consonant sounds and about 20 vowel sounds.
